hem require passing through a number of obstacles, and are themselves extremely resistant to magic, fire, and cold.  Shambling cubes of that level may also have it, but they can be extraordinarily hard, splitting twice and requiring you to kill 11 NPCs, some of which are immune to magic -- stay away from them.<br>
<br>
Your best bet it to partner with a melee and keep the sentry rooms after the pool room clear. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 6/2/02 1:16:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhappyfeetfunkmaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Happyfeet Funkmaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 4:41:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26358.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Square helm - where and how?</span><hr size=1> I've only seen Square helms (and other items on that loot table) drop from named wyverns and Oct Cubes...so basicly anything past that first Wurm you see as you go up.<br>
